      {
        "type": "post",
        "description": "Today I had the most profound media experience \ud83e\udd14\ud83c\udf99 \u2013\u00a0I attended my first podcast AMA call with Lenny Rachitsky and Shreman Shrestha from Lenny's Newsletter. \n\n1. It was incredibly authentic and unproduced \u2013\u00a0and that made it perfect and special. \n\n2. It likely only costed Lenny an hour of his time too \u2013 No editing, no scripting. \n\n3. I was allowed into the inner-circle \u2013 As an ex-product manager, I've tuned into Lenny's podcast over the years and there's something exciting/ valuable/ humanizing about just being in a room (even virtual) with those you've listened to for some time. \n\n4. Most of all, I felt like I got a chance to connect with my tribe (people like me) \u2013\u00a0and learn through their thoughtful questions and experience how moved they felt from Lenny's work too. \n\nAs someone that's focused on building the future of media experiences,  I was transported from consuming a podcast to being included as part of Lenny' story \u2013\u00a0where Lenny took me behind his scenes and shared some of his inner workings and learnings. \n\nNow I feel even more pulled to replicate this feeling and connect people to the shows and tribes they love \u2013\u00a0so more of us can feel this too! \n\nIf you're a business/ product thinker. I highly recommend tuning into Lenny's podcast here: (https://lnkd.in/eMWhAn_V). Not just to learn from him and his guests - but also to experience the future of media through his tech stack and inclusive community experiences where his community has become his product as much as his incredible content! \ud83e\udd2f \n\n#podcast #podcastcommunity #podcasters",
        "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7140800439792345090?updateEntityUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afs_feedUpdate%3A%28V2%2Curn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7140800439792345090%29",
